<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Million" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Million</orth> (ordinarily dissyll.; trisyll. in <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 36</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 49</bibl>). 1) ten hundred thousand: <cit><quote>a crooked figure may attest in little place a m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 49</bibl></cit>. == a sum of ten hundred thousand pounds: <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.155" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 147</bibl>.<lb />2) any very great number, an infinite number: <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.241" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 241</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 14, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 143</bibl>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>a m. of manners,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 105</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a m. of beating,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 62</bibl></cit>. <emph>the m.</emph> == the multitude: <cit><quote>the play pleased not the m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.457" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 457</bibl></cit>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 7</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 3, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 68</bibl>. With <cit><quote>of:</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 53.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 53, 2</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.304" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 304</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>